Sportswear is fundamentally Axis fashion. Coco Chanel, Rudolf and Adi Dassler, etc. "Menswear" is an attempt of Churchillian overburdened Victorian-era Evangelion plugsuits to reassert themselves against the lightness of German culture. Tracksuits are better than neckties-nooses.

Suits constrict and prevent spontaneity. In track pants and a t-shirt you are capable of suddenly jumping, performing random athletic acts, doing a few pull-ups while on a walk. Sportswear is clothing meant for a culture of joy, recreation, comfort. Good riddance of boring suits.
